The HS girls and boys Cross Country teams competed Friday the 4th at the Carl Albert Invitational. Our teams run next at the OBU Invitational this Saturday the 12th.
WAY TO GO GUYS AND GALS!!!! WE ARE PROUD OF YOU!!!!

post_text:
BIG NEWS FROM SODEXO!!!!

Harrah schools will be offering Free meals (both Breakfast & Lunch), to all students.

* This is being funded through USDA. They announced Sept 3, that we can back out charges as of Sept 1, this will run through Dec 12, 2020, or "until funding from USDA runs out"

* We still need to collect all free/reduced forms for a couple of reasons, 1) Other school government funding programs are determined by our free/reduced percentage. 2) Once the funding runs out from USDA we will have to go back to charging our normal prices, whether free, reduced or full pay.

* Students will receive 1 breakfast and 1 lunch meal free per day. If a 2nd meal, any ala cart, or an adult meal are to be purchased they will be charged accordingly.

If you have any questions please contact Nela Edwards at nedwards@harrahschools.com or 347-2825.

post_text:
More exciting news from the National FFA Organization for the Harrah FFA Chapter!

Ryen Macy was named a NATIONAL FINALIST for her Service Learning Proficiency! She will be representing Oklahoma and competing this month against three other states. Wish her luck!

Abby Burris represented Oklahoma and was named a Gold Emblem Individual for her Wildlife Management Proficiency.

Hannah Dozier represented Oklahoma and was named a Silver Emblem Individual for her Equine Science Placement Proficiency.

Agricultural Proficiency Awards honor FFA members who, through supervised agricultural experiences, have developed specialized skills that they can apply toward their future careers.

Congratulations to each of you. We are very proud of you ladies!!!

post_text:
Harrah FFA Chapter Named 2020 3-Star National Chapter

The Harrah FFA Chapter received the 3-Star National Chapter ranking from the National FFA Organization. This is the highest award an FFA chapter can receive.

This program recognizes outstanding FFA chapters from throughout the country that actively implement the mission and strategies of the FFA. These chapters improve chapter operations using the National Quality FFA Chapter Standards
and a Program of Activities that emphasizes growing leaders, building communities and strengthening agriculture. Chapters are rewarded for providing educational experiences for the entire membership.

Preparing for potential interruptions during this current school year, we are asking the community to give us feedback on how a potential BLENDED LEARNING MODEL might serve your family best. All options will have an A/B schedule where only half of the school population would be in the building on any given day. When students are learning from home in this setting, it is remote learning or DISTANCE LEARNING. The district will work to ensure that siblings and families would be on the same schedule. THIS IS ONLY A SURVEY and all Brick-and Mortar students will be attending classes on campus until otherwise notified. Thank you!

VSE Harrah
August 13 at 8:05 PM ·

First off, thank you so much for your patience and kindness today during pick-up and drop-off. Our pick-up system had a glitch that will, hopefully, be fixed tomorrow. We have a Plan B if not. You will do the same thing with one change that we implemented for some of you today. The purple line indicates an extension of our path for all cars dropping off in the morning. Kindergarten and first grade parents should use it when picking up. Just a reminder, please do not get in line to pick up your kindergartener and/or first grader until 2:50 at the earliest. If not, it blocks our pre-k from picking up at their earlier release time and blocks our school buses. Kindergarten and first grade do not release until 3:05 PM. Thank you for helping us! 💙🐾

shared_text:
Harrah-HighSchool Softball
May 4 at 11:20 AM ·

Please join Coach Dotson & Coach Jack in congratulating our 2020 Harrah Slowpitch All-Staters!!

💙🎉💙🎉💙🎉💙🎉💙🎉💙🎉💙🎉
Stephanie McDonald and Sarena Sanders
💙🎉💙🎉💙🎉💙🎉💙🎉💙🎉💙🎉

We are immensely proud of them. These two girls put in the WORK it takes to be recognized for this amazing honor. They are both true blue Panthers with a big love for the game and an even bigger love for their team. We didn’t get our season like we should have.. if we had, you’d be watching us in the state tournament this week, I have no doubt. But I am elated that these two were able to receive the honor of all-state, even without being able to enjoy their senior seasons.

They will both be playing college softball, so they’re not done yet! Look for Steph at Oklahoma Baptist University and Sarena at Independence Community College in Kansas.

So much love to you both and good luck in your future endeavors!!
#alwaysapanther 💙🥎

post_text:
To All Our HS Track kids,

Hey, guys rest assured I have all the gear you ordered through Trendy T’s and Mr. Hughey’s order (Macco) and your beef jerky from our fundraiser. I’ll hold on to everything until I see you again. Seniors, we’ll figure out a way to get your stuff to you! I didn’t want you guys wondering about these things.

Well...what started as a very promising year came crashing down to a very sad ending. Believe me, when I tell you losing this Track season is just as tough on your coaches as it is on you all! To my Seniors...I feel the worst for you! A sudden ending for you guys that showed so much promise.

To my Cross Country athletes: I’ve reached out to some of you with the Summer workout schedule. If you didn’t get a copy and want to run CC next Fall, email me!

If anyone wants to talk or just share something with me, please email me at chilburn@harrahschools.com

Sincerely,
Coach Hilburn and Coach Blackburn

post_text: Today's CRE LIL' PANTHER OF THE DAY is.....Kameren Coast from Mrs. Vernon's 2nd-grade class. Kameren is an awesome young man. He loved being first to class in the mornings so he could sneak up and scare me. Then he would wait for the next student to walk through the door to "surprise" as well. His smile is contagious! Kameren is a hard worker who cares greatly about getting everything "just right". That explains his beautiful handwriting. Along with being fun-loving and conscientious about his work, Kameren also has a wonderful heart. He is a loyal friend. Kameren I miss seeing you daily. I am proud of all your hard work and progress you've made this year. Keep it up! CRE ❤'s you!

post_text:
Moments ago the Oklahoma State Board of Education held a special meeting to authorize the closure of all Oklahoma schools beginning March 17 and lasting until April 6. The State Department of Education and the State Health Department will be closely monitoring the COVID-19 situation with other state health experts to determine if it will be necessary to extend this closure.

We know closing schools has a significant impact on families, and we are committed to the safety of our students and staff at Harrah Public Schools. During this closure all school activities (including games, trips, activities, practices, etc.) are canceled until further notice.

In the coming days more information will be made available to staff and parents concerning plans to address specific issues this closure will create. We will continue to keep everyone advised as these developments are happening.

post_text:
I am sure everyone is aware about the concerns surrounding the coronavirus. This has led to a lot of questions and an excessive amount of absences at many of our sites. Although the recommendation from state health professionals is to keep schools open, we cannot ignore the fact that many parents will choose to keep their kids at home tomorrow. As a result, Harrah Public Schools will be closed on Friday, March 13th.

This closing will not extend our school year. We had one more inclement weather day built in our calendar. Over Spring Break, all facilities will be closed for all activities, events, and practices. During this time, we will continue to monitor developments related to COVID-19.

Have a great Spring Break!!!!

post_text:
Congratulations to the Pride of Harrah High School and the HMS Band for their successes in competition yesterday. The Middle School Band played two difficult pieces of music and received a 1-2-2 Excellent rating on stage and received a Superior in sight-reading. Because of this, they were awarded a "Superior Sight Reading" OSSAA Plaque.

The High School Band also played two difficult pieces and achieved a 1-1-1 on stage, earning them a Superior rating; they also received a superior rating in sight-reading. This is a very high honor, qualifying them for state competition. State Band contest will be at ECU April 2 or April 3.

The amount of growth the band has gone through this year has been astounding. We are proud of you! Time to head to state!

Spring Break 2021 trip to Ireland and Scotland

Anyone with students 8th grade and up are invited to attend an informational meeting for our Spring Break 2021 trip to Ireland and Scotland. We will discuss the details of the trip, travel expectations and cost. The meetings last about 45 minutes.

This will be my 6th trip overseas and I hope that if you have any interest or know anyone who might, I encourage you to attend this brief meeting.

The meeting will be in the Art room behind the tennis courts at Harrah High School on Thursday, February 27th at 6 PM

Just a few pics of where we will be going. Dublin, Belfast, and Edinburgh

Justin Harkey
jharkey@harrahschools.com
Art Department Head
Harrah High School

post_text:
On Sunday, January 19th, three Harrah High School juniors were honored at VFW Post 7192 in Midwest City for their Voice of Democracy audio essays. The students wrote for the theme:

What Makes America Great & recorded their essays for submission.

Lexi Malaske won 1st place in the local competition, Kailey Jones won 2nd place, & Avery Boston won 3rd place. Lexi's & Kailey's essays went on to district competition where Kailey won 3rd place.

All students were awarded monetary prizes for their essays. Pictured are (from left to right): Harrah High School Principal, David Hairell, VFW Senior Vice Commander John Rogers, Kailey Jones, Lexi Malaske, Avery Boston, Bonnie Wheeler VFW Auxillary President, and Carrie Milligan, English III & AP Literature teacher.

post_text:
The wrestling team has been working hard all break. The high school traveled to Louisiana over the break to wrestle in the Lone Survivor National Tournament, we finished 2nd as a team with 4 individual champions. Cade Carter, Kyler Damron, Hunter Mauldin, and first-year starter Seth Goodman. Hunter Mauldin was also voted by all the coaches as the Outstanding Wrestler of the tournament for the most dominating performance in the tournament. Hunter's finals match was against an undefeated returning state champion from Louisiana, whom he beat 11-5. Also placing was Wheeler Williams, Braeden Williams, Chadlee Humphries, Michael Yarbrough, Jude Stone, Patrick Montgomery, and Mort Barber.

WAY TO GO!!!!!!

shared_text:
Harrah Public Schools added 10 new photos — in Wynnewood, Oklahoma.
January 6 at 4:03 PM · Wynnewood, OK ·

The Team Harrah Livestock show team was very busy over the break. This past Saturday they traveled to the Wynnewood Jackpot show, with over 400 hogs there it made for a long but successful day for the crew. Highlights at Wynnewood were:

Britney Oehler Res breed champion Berk
Hannah Dozier Res breed champion Herf
Ava Shamrock Breed champion Poland
Ava Shamrock Res breed champion Spot
Justin Erbin Res breed champion Spot
Hunter Carey Res breed champion cross

The team took 47 head and 41 of them placed in the top 5 of their classes, big time day!!

On Sunday the team showed at the Crown Auto World classic in Bristow, with right at 300 head it made for another long day but successful one, highlights were:

Kinley Claytor, breed champion berk
Britney Oehler, Res breed champion berk
Hannah Dozier, res breed herf
Ava Shamrock, breed champion Poland
Hunter Carey, res breed champion cross and then Bronze overall market hog.

The team took 28 head and 24 placed in the top 5 of their classes, another big time day.

post_text:
Ms. Winings first hour class College Career Math Readiness, had the opportunity to participate in an activity this Monday.

The lesson was designed to give students the experience of finding a line of best fit and to use and apply their knowledge of linear functions. Their task was to use rubber bands and a water balloon (the "jumper") to simulate a bungee jump.

Data was collected in the classroom with some short jumps and their job was to estimate the number of rubber bands it would take for a safe but "thrill-seeking" jump off the bleachers at the football field, 225 inch jump, coming as close as possible to the ground without touching it.

They definitely had some thrilling jumps!

post_text: Are you in the mood for some amazing smoked ribs? Well, let the Harrah FFA & 4-H Booster Club help ease the pain of the holiday season! The Harrah FFA & 4-H booster club is selling racks of smoked ribs just in time for the holiday season. Ribs are prepaid by December 16th and will be available for pick up at Nowakowski Processing (right next to the feed mill) on December 23rd between 1:00-5:30 that afternoon just in time to help with the Holiday meal. If you have any questions, please contact Mr. Carey at bcarey@harrahschools.com.
